    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-07T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-07T05:00:00-05:00" n="731"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d731">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/2386: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-07T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 7, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 7—6:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>352. Letter signed by Vasconcellos, President of Committee of Coordination,
                    addressed to me dated November 6, reads as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I have the honor to transmit to you herewith, in accordance with the
                            decision of the Coordination Committee, the resolutions and decisions
                            adopted at the close of its second session on November 2,<note n="68"
                                xml:id="d731fn1">League of Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official
                                    Journal</hi>, Special Supplement No. 146, pp. 7–13.</note> the
                            minutes of that meeting,<note n="69" xml:id="d731fn2">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>
                            </note> and the replies of governments to the five proposals adopted
                            during the first session.<note n="69" xml:id="d731fn3">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>
                            </note> I would be grateful if you would be good enough to transmit this
                            documentation to the Secretary of State in Washington.</p>
                        <p>I need not add that I continue to be at the disposal of the United States
                            Government, in accordance with my letter of October 21, addressed to the
                            Secretary of State.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Coordinate letter and enclosures being forwarded by mail steamship <hi
                        rend="italic">Berengaria</hi> sailing 13th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
